.TH QUOTAI 1 "May 2026" "quotai" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
quotai \- show Z.ai quota usage and exact reset windows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B quotai
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B quotai
queries the Z.ai quota endpoint and prints current quota usage, remaining
capacity, and reset timing. The default output is a human-readable terminal
view; JSON, JSON Lines, compact, and raw modes are available for automation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show the program version.
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-json
Output formatted JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-jsonl
Output JSON Lines.
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Print the raw API response.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-compact
Print one compact line per quota.
.TP
.B \-\-no-color
Disable ANSI color output.
.TP
.B \-z, \-\-timezone \fITIMEZONE\fR
Display reset times in an IANA timezone.
.TP
.B \-\-api-key \fIKEY\fR
Z.ai API key. Defaults to the ZAI_API_KEY environment variable.
.TP
.B \-\-api-url \fIURL\fR
Quota endpoint URL. Defaults to the ZAI_API_URL environment variable or the
built-in Z.ai quota endpoint.
.TP
.B \-w, \-\-watch \fISECONDS\fR
Refresh output every N seconds.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-threshold \fIPERCENT\fR
Exit with code 2 if any quota usage is at or above PERCENT.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ZAI_API_KEY
Bearer token used to query the quota endpoint.
.TP
.B ZAI_API_URL
Optional replacement quota endpoint.
.TP
.B ZAI_TIMEZONE
Default display timezone.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or input error.
.TP
.B 2
Threshold exceeded.
.SH AUTHOR
Simon Oakes
